version_description: Tabbed from 1997 the last time Donnie Munro sang live with Runrig as lead singer,Play with acoustic picking guitar ,or clean electric rhythm again picking strings.
Really simple celtic folk song by Runrig to play on acoustic guitar https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7bU81YyRME8.
Played with electric guitar with tremolo,slap back and chorus effects,a little fuzz can be added for "hearthammer" refrain,alternatively use the strum guide for a "folk" feel.
Simple Tune played on Capo 2,from the album the Cutter And The Clan,Live version uses Capo on 4th.
Acoustic Guitar Simple guitar pluck to suit,or use strum pattern above to suit,a simple ,reflective optimistic tune.
From Runrigs 1st album Highland Collection ,play with acoustic guitar ,the track is enhanced with an accordian and Mandolin to give it a celtic/folk feel.
Played with acoustic guitar but can also be played with electric guitar with Fuzz/Chorus effects for more of a rock sound.
Traditional Celtic folk song from early Runrig years,play on acoustic guitar,finger pick chorus. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GK-7i-yz8FM.
Play this with Capo on 1st fret in key G,can be played with clean electric guitar with chorus effect,or on accoustic to give a folk feel.

song_name: Nightfall On Marsco  S Tu Mo Leannan

version_description: Worked out the chords from the live version but it should be the right key on the studio version.
Folk rock song best played on acoustic guitar or clean electric with compression.You Tube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cb4BtxTb1rw.

Traditional celtic song,easily played on acoustic guitar on the outro lead riff it sounds better using an E-Bow,the same riff could be used on the instrumental break as well so as to replace the recordings accordian.You Tube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UMBEIoIIQnU.
Very simple song to play,no capo required,best played on acoustic guitar or electric with a little chorus effect.There is lead guitar on outro which could be ad libbed to suit using G F# E A D.
Acoustic guitar simple string plucking BPM around 114 ,if electro acoustic reverb and chorus effects https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ptkwMysv_DA.
Celtic folk song ideally played on acoustic guitar to give a "folk" feel,alternatively played with electric "clean "guitar with a little chorus effect.
Very easy, busking type song that can be played with acoustic guitar or Mandolin.Capo can be added to 3rd and transposed on here to make it easy for beginners.
